Package com.edugility.nomen

Provides classes and interfaces for working with names of all varieties.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MutableNamed
    A Named that permits additions and removals.
    Named
    An owner of Names that can retrieve them efficiently when asked for them by NameType.
    Valued
    Indicates that an implementation is capable of reporting its value as a String.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractNamed
    An implementation of the MutableNamed interface that uses a NameSupport delegate internally.
    AbstractValued
    A Serializable Valued implementation that correctly implements the AbstractValued.equals(Object) and AbstractValued.hashCode() methods.
    Name
    A Serializable AbstractValued implementation that is a combination of a NameValue and the Named that it is currently assigned to.
    NameOwnershipMonitor
    A special-purpose PropertyChangeListener that ensures that if a Name's ownership changes, then all entries within a Map that reference it are removed.
    NameSupport
    An object that manages Names on behalf of some Named.
    NameType
    An AbstractValued implementation that serves as a key within a Named to identify particular Name instances.
    NameValue
    An AbstractValued implementation that represents the value of a name of something.

Package com.edugility.nomen Description

Provides classes and interfaces for working with names of all varieties.
